From: CHIP Builder <chip@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: dts: sun5i-r8-chip: build base dtb with __symbols__ (-@)

The CHIP DIP device-tree overlays are applied by u-boot (`fdt apply`) at boot,
which can only resolve their label references (&keyboard, &i2c0, ...) if the
base dtb carries a __symbols__ node. Set DTC_FLAGS_sun5i-r8-chip := -@ so dtc
emits it for this one dtb (same mechanism the Raspberry Pi dtbs use).

Signed-off-by: CHIP Builder <chip@localhost>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/Makefile | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/Makefile
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/Makefile
@@ -1,4 +1,9 @@
 # SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0
+
+# Build the CHIP base dtb with __symbols__ (dtc -@) so u-boot's `fdt apply` can
+# resolve overlay label references -- needed to apply DIP device-tree overlays
+# at boot from the NAND boot script.
+DTC_FLAGS_sun5i-r8-chip := -@
 dtb-$(CONFIG_MACH_SUN4I) += \
 	sun4i-a10-a1000.dtb \
 	sun4i-a10-ba10-tvbox.dtb \
